1
00:00:07,750 --> 00:00:10,208
[Karasuma] Why did you become a lawyer,
Mr. Kujo?

2
00:00:13,291 --> 00:00:15,541
Are you interviewing me again?

3
00:00:20,291 --> 00:00:22,916
All right, let me ask you
the same question.

4
00:00:24,083 --> 00:00:27,000
Why did you become a lawyer, Mr. Karasuma?

5
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,458
It started a long time ago.

6
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:33,333
There was a trial I attended.

7
00:00:33,416 --> 00:00:37,083
When you killed your neighbor,
Toshiko Nakabayashi, with an axe,

8
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:40,125
you were yelling some strange things,
weren't you?

9
00:00:40,666 --> 00:00:44,083
According to the testimony
of your next-door neighbor, you screamed,

10
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:50,416
"All my private emails are on the internet
for everyone to see,

11
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:51,916
you gossipy old hag."

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,208
- [laughing]
- [prosecutor] "You did this to me."

13
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:55,750
[unsettling music playing]

14
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:58,708
[prosecutor] Why did you kill
Toshiko Nakabayashi?

15
00:00:59,208 --> 00:01:00,666
Is this the reason?

16
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:02,250
The reason?

17
00:01:02,958 --> 00:01:05,000
She was the mastermind
of the world's overlords.

18
00:01:06,208 --> 00:01:08,125
She kept my room
under constant surveillance

19
00:01:08,208 --> 00:01:09,583
with that triangle eye.

20
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,750
The world's overlords want to kill
every last one of us

21
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:15,250
with electromagnetic waves.

22
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:16,916
I learned about their evil plan

23
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,666
and exposed the mastermind
to save the world!

24
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:21,333
So she wanted vengeance.

25
00:01:21,416 --> 00:01:23,541
She attacked me
with an electromagnetic weapon.

26
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:24,541
What could I do?

27
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:26,625
I killed her in self-defense.

28
00:01:27,125 --> 00:01:28,375
Can't you see?

29
00:01:29,291 --> 00:01:33,583
You said you were taking
your medication every day.

30
00:01:35,125 --> 00:01:39,666
You also testified that the medication
makes you confused, isn't that right?

31
00:01:40,541 --> 00:01:44,208
But you stopped going to the hospital
a month before the incident, correct?

32
00:01:44,291 --> 00:01:45,708
At the time of the crimes,

33
00:01:45,791 --> 00:01:47,625
you weren't taking
any medication at all, right

34
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:48,916
- [screams]
- [judge] Order!

35
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,333
- The defendant will return to his seat!
- What's that? Hey!

36
00:01:51,416 --> 00:01:53,083
What did you say? What did you say?

37
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:54,750
[sobbing]

38
00:01:54,833 --> 00:01:56,541
If I may continue.

39
00:01:57,458 --> 00:01:59,000
On the day in question,

40
00:01:59,791 --> 00:02:02,041
what was your reason
for boarding the bullet train

41
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:03,875
after you stole the victim's ticket?

42
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:05,875
Orders from on high!

43
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:08,875
A voice spoke to me loud and clear.

44
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:12,916
It said the person who would sit beside me
was the god of darkness!

45
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:16,458
[prosecutor] As you rode the train
that day,

46
00:02:16,541 --> 00:02:19,708
why did you use an axe
to kill Katsunobu Karasuma,

47
00:02:19,791 --> 00:02:22,541
who heroically tried to stop your rampage?

48
00:02:22,625 --> 00:02:23,875
[panting]

49
00:02:23,958 --> 00:02:24,958
I became…

50
00:02:25,041 --> 00:02:25,916
[disturbed laughter]

51
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,291
…the world's savior.

52
00:02:27,375 --> 00:02:28,875
[laughing continues]

53
00:02:31,958 --> 00:02:33,375
I am…

54
00:02:33,458 --> 00:02:35,750
- [judge] Bailiff! Restrain him!
- …the savior! The savior!

55
00:02:35,833 --> 00:02:40,125
I'm the savior! I'm the savior!

56
00:02:40,208 --> 00:02:41,750
[poignant music playing]

57
00:02:41,833 --> 00:02:45,458
The circumstances of this case
are vile and abhorrent,

58
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:49,250
and the defendant bears a great degree
of criminal responsibility.

59
00:02:49,791 --> 00:02:52,500
To match the severity
of the punishment to the crimes

60
00:02:52,583 --> 00:02:54,750
and to deter others
from acts of this nature,

61
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:58,166
the court finds it has… no alternative

62
00:02:58,250 --> 00:03:02,291
but to impose the death penalty
on the defendant.

63
00:03:03,916 --> 00:03:07,000
The reasons for this decision
are as follows.

64
00:03:11,708 --> 00:03:13,333
[Kujo] <i>I remember.</i>

65
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:18,291
I remember that trial. I was there.

66
00:03:19,125 --> 00:03:20,208
[Karasuma] I know.

67
00:03:21,458 --> 00:03:22,625
That's why I'm here.

68
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:27,416
You helped us so much, Attorney Sayama.
Thank you for everything.

69
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,583
No, please.

70
00:03:29,166 --> 00:03:31,958
Katsunobu Karasuma got the justice
he deserved.

71
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:33,041
That's all that matters.

72
00:03:33,125 --> 00:03:34,208
Yes.

73
00:03:34,291 --> 00:03:35,375
In my view,

74
00:03:35,458 --> 00:03:39,250
the turning point was when Prosecutor
Kurama cross-examined the defendant.

75
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:40,875
[upbeat music playing]

76
00:03:40,958 --> 00:03:42,125
Uh, Shinji,

77
00:03:42,916 --> 00:03:45,625
Attorney Sayama and I
are going to go pay our respects

78
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:47,791
to the defense team and their supporters.

79
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:50,166
I'll be back in a sec, okay?

80
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:51,333
Okay.

81
00:03:51,416 --> 00:03:52,250
[Sayama] Mm.

82
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:54,291
- Right, shall we?
- Well, then, yes.

83
00:03:57,625 --> 00:04:00,708
[young Kujo] What a load of crap.
No way the death penalty should apply.

84
00:04:00,791 --> 00:04:03,875
He gets that smug look,
all holier than thou. The stupid old fart.

85
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:07,041
Hey! Where do you get off
badmouthing our father?

86
00:04:07,916 --> 00:04:11,666
[young Kujo] Don't you get what happened?
When the defendant was questioned?

87
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:15,333
Article 39 of the Penal Code,
not guilty by reason of insanity.

88
00:04:15,416 --> 00:04:17,333
That guy was a textbook example.

89
00:04:17,416 --> 00:04:18,541
He should've been acquitted.

90
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:19,625
You're such a poser.

91
00:04:19,708 --> 00:04:21,958
You sound like a kid who read
one page from the legal code.

92
00:04:22,041 --> 00:04:25,625
All those news channels made a big deal
about the grief of the families.

93
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:27,708
They swayed public opinion,
and the court ate it up.

94
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:30,791
It was a trial by media.
Emotions counted more than facts did.

95
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:32,500
That's the problem.

96
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:36,208
When the human element comes into play,
it's not just about the law anymore.

97
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:40,375
That's why we need to keep public opinion
out of the courtroom.

98
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:42,250
[brother] Enough with the whining, Taiza.

99
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:45,416
Save the big talk
for after you pass the bar exam.

100
00:04:49,125 --> 00:04:51,166
This time he got the death sentence,

101
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:54,458
but if it's Attorney Nagaragi,
he'll get life imprisonment in the appeal.

102
00:05:00,166 --> 00:05:02,166
[music fades]

103
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,166
If it's okay, I'll stick around for a bit.

104
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:16,666
Okay, sure.

105
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:19,333
[theme music playing]

106
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:02,791
Here. Check it out.

107
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:06,500
Tonight's a party party! [chuckles]

108
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,166
[sniffs]

109
00:06:13,291 --> 00:06:14,500
Looking good.

110
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:15,666
Awesome, dude.

111
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:20,666
[man] Excuse me!

112
00:06:22,916 --> 00:06:23,958
Do you have a moment?

113
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:25,083
Huh?

114
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:27,041
What do you… what you got there?

115
00:06:28,541 --> 00:06:30,708
Uh, it's just… it's just candy.

116
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:32,791
Do you mind
if we have a look inside the bag, sir?

117
00:06:32,875 --> 00:06:34,333
I told you. It's… it's just candy.

118
00:06:34,416 --> 00:06:35,875
- We just want to confirm.
- So sorry.

119
00:06:35,958 --> 00:06:37,541
Don't get mad at me, okay? No. I'm sorry.

120
00:06:37,625 --> 00:06:39,625
I'm not mad. Take it easy!

121
00:06:39,708 --> 00:06:41,541
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

122
00:06:41,625 --> 00:06:43,875
[Kujo] Excuse me. May I have a moment?

123
00:06:43,958 --> 00:06:45,791
- [Sogabe] I'm sorry. I'm sorry…
- [cop] Hey.

124
00:06:45,875 --> 00:06:47,083
What are you doing?

125
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:48,875
Do you wanna get charged with obstruction?

126
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:53,125
Filming for a legitimate reason
is not considered

127
00:06:53,208 --> 00:06:55,583
obstructing the performance
of public duty.

128
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:59,250
I'm preserving evidence in case
there's an illegal search and seizure.

129
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:02,041
- Who the hell do you think you are, huh?
- [camera chimes]

130
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:03,708
[upbeat music playing]

131
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:07,208
A good lawyer, but a… a bad person.

132
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:08,666
You're a lawyer?

133
00:07:10,208 --> 00:07:11,500
I'm sure you're all aware

134
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:15,291
that he is not obligated to comply with
a simple stop-and-frisk, correct?

135
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:18,750
Detaining someone for any length
of time against their will

136
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:22,041
is considered an unlawful arrest
unless you've got a warrant.

137
00:07:22,125 --> 00:07:23,583
You do it, you break the law.

138
00:07:24,958 --> 00:07:28,458
If you decide to pursue this,
you better have a warrant with you.

139
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:31,250
Excuse us.

140
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:37,833
[music fades]

141
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:40,666
KUJO LAW OFFICE

142
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,125
[slurps]

143
00:07:43,208 --> 00:07:44,458
[sighs]

144
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:49,291
What's the matter? Too spicy for you?

145
00:07:49,375 --> 00:07:54,500
Uh, no. Uh, would it bother you if I,
uh, slurp my soup?

146
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,083
Go ahead.

147
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:57,708
[slurps]

148
00:07:57,791 --> 00:07:58,666
[sighs]

149
00:07:58,750 --> 00:07:59,750
[sniffs]

150
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:03,416
Mr. Sogabe,
would you prefer bottled water or tea?

151
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:06,166
[Sogabe] Well, I'm good with tap water.

152
00:08:13,166 --> 00:08:14,708
Sorry. Thank you.

153
00:08:15,291 --> 00:08:18,125
You've done some serious time,
haven't you?

154
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:19,833
Huh?

155
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:23,166
So, how long have you been out?

156
00:08:24,125 --> 00:08:25,875
[chuckles] How'd you know I did time?

157
00:08:26,541 --> 00:08:28,666
You ask permission before you slurp.

158
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,750
You can't choose what you want to drink.

159
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:32,708
Those are hallmarks of someone

160
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:35,416
who has learned to obey
the rules and codes of prison.

161
00:08:37,125 --> 00:08:38,041
[slurps]

162
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:40,083
Nah, that ain't it.

163
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:42,416
[exclaiming] My bad! Ah!

164
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,041
[Kujo] Mmm.

165
00:08:44,541 --> 00:08:46,625
- Oh, so sorry.
- Mm-mm.

166
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:47,541
Here.

167
00:08:48,666 --> 00:08:49,708
PIECE OF SHIT

168
00:08:49,791 --> 00:08:51,708
[Kujo] That's a peculiar tattoo.

169
00:08:51,791 --> 00:08:52,791
[Sogabe] Huh?

170
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:53,750
Oh.

171
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,875
- [cell phone rings]
- [Sogabe exclaims]

172
00:08:58,916 --> 00:09:00,333
Oh, hello?

173
00:09:00,416 --> 00:09:01,833
[man] Two rings.

174
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:04,708
You pick up on the first one, you dimwit!

175
00:09:04,791 --> 00:09:05,958
Oh, sorry.

176
00:09:06,041 --> 00:09:07,666
[man] <i>The customer is waiting.</i>

177
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:10,541
<i>Get your ass in gear</i>
<i>and deliver those veggies, you hear me?</i>

178
00:09:10,625 --> 00:09:11,458
Uh-huh.

179
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:15,166
You caught some heat out there
because your head was up your asshole!

180
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:18,250
Plus you're gonna cough up
the cash for the lawyer.

181
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,958
Sogabe,

182
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:23,583
you better prepare yourself
to receive the tattoo of shame!

183
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:25,541
[whines fearfully]

184
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:27,458
Uh.

185
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:29,458
Right. I'm so sorry.

186
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:33,000
[grunts] Thanks for the food!

187
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:37,041
[panting]

188
00:09:37,125 --> 00:09:38,166
Ah, oh!

189
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,875
- Excuse me.
- [Sogabe] Excuse me.

190
00:09:45,416 --> 00:09:46,291
[sighs]

191
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:54,375
Mr. Kujo,
was that Sota Sogabe I just saw leaving?

192
00:09:54,458 --> 00:09:57,250
Yeah. You know him, Mr. Karasuma?

193
00:09:57,333 --> 00:10:00,666
Yeah. I defended him about six years ago.

194
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:09,458
[Kujo] He forgot this.

195
00:10:16,041 --> 00:10:17,125
It's marijuana.

196
00:10:17,208 --> 00:10:18,375
What?

197
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:25,375
[sighs]

198
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:26,875
Tell me what he was charged with.

199
00:10:28,416 --> 00:10:32,916
First-degree robbery.
Causing bodily injury. He got six years.

200
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:36,750
[upbeat music playing]

201
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:39,500
[Karasuma] <i>Back then,</i>
<i>Sota Sogabe was 21 years old.</i>

202
00:10:39,583 --> 00:10:43,125
<i>He was using 16-year-old boys</i>
<i>to pull a string of robberies.</i>

203
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:48,250
However, the truth is, Mr. Sogabe
wasn't the brains of the operation.

204
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:51,916
[panting]

205
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:56,875
Sorry.

206
00:10:57,708 --> 00:10:58,625
Ah.

207
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:00,500
Sogabe.

208
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,208
- Where are the veggies?
- Huh?

209
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:07,041
The lawyer! I forgot them there!

210
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:08,708
- What?
- [Sogabe cries out]

211
00:11:08,791 --> 00:11:10,208
- [man] Take that!
- [Sogabe cries out]

212
00:11:10,291 --> 00:11:12,500
- Sorry! Sorry, sorry, sorry.
- Hey!

213
00:11:12,583 --> 00:11:16,083
You're gonna get the tattoo of shame,
you hear?

214
00:11:16,916 --> 00:11:19,208
[Karasuma] <i>The mastermind</i>
<i>was Suguru Kanemoto.</i>

215
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:22,833
<i>He's the son of a former Yakuza</i>
<i>and was once an aspiring sumo wrestler.</i>

216
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:26,083
Kanemoto and his gang
committed robbery and assault

217
00:11:26,166 --> 00:11:28,500
and used Mr. Sogabe
as the fall guy in the end.

218
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:30,458
I see.

219
00:11:31,916 --> 00:11:33,291
What was he doing here?

220
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:37,666
This Kanemoto guy you mention
was Mibu's underling, it would appear.

221
00:11:38,166 --> 00:11:40,791
I was asked to help him
get out of a police questioning.

222
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:46,875
It seems like Suguru Kanemoto
is using Mr. Sogabe

223
00:11:46,958 --> 00:11:48,750
to deliver drugs to his clients.

224
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,958
That's where the risk
of arrest is highest.

225
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:56,333
It's so sad. He does all that hard time,
and Kanemoto's using him again.

226
00:11:56,958 --> 00:11:59,791
There's got to be some way
we can rescue Mr. Sogabe.

227
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,000
You're being arrogant.

228
00:12:03,083 --> 00:12:04,000
Huh?

229
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:07,750
As if lawyers can save anyone.

230
00:12:09,166 --> 00:12:10,166
What do you mean?

231
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,291
How about a cup of coffee?

232
00:12:18,416 --> 00:12:20,750
How do Mr. Sogabe
and Kanemoto know each other?

233
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,416
Through their fathers.

234
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:24,791
Back in the day,

235
00:12:24,875 --> 00:12:27,541
Kanemoto's dad turned Sogabe's dad
into his little slave

236
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:29,208
by beating the hell out of him.

237
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:30,125
[coughing]

238
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:32,625
[thug] Suguru,
what's this guy even good for?

239
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:36,166
[Kanemoto] A great leader can make use
of even the most worthless subordinate.

240
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:37,500
A great leader?

241
00:12:37,583 --> 00:12:39,208
- [Kanemoto] Right now…
- [groaning]

242
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:43,833
…I've got him delivering my dope
for the same pay as a pizza delivery guy.

243
00:12:43,916 --> 00:12:45,083
[thug] For real?

244
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:47,291
He's earning peanuts
and he knows he could get busted?

245
00:12:47,875 --> 00:12:51,041
Our families are from
the same neighborhood.

246
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:54,958
His loser dad used to get shaken down
by my old man all the time.

247
00:12:55,625 --> 00:13:00,833
He'd scam him in blackjack games.
Poor guy didn't even know the rules.

248
00:13:00,916 --> 00:13:02,625
[Kanemoto and thug laughing]

249
00:13:02,708 --> 00:13:03,583
[Kanemoto] Hey, you.

250
00:13:03,666 --> 00:13:04,666
[Sogabe grunts]

251
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:08,291
Hey, Sogabe! If you can't follow orders,

252
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:11,500
I'm gonna ink you
in the same spot as your dad.

253
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:13,083
- No, please, stop.
- [Kanemoto laughs]

254
00:13:13,166 --> 00:13:14,666
What do you mean by the same spot?

255
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:17,333
Yeah, when my old man was in a mood,

256
00:13:17,416 --> 00:13:21,666
he used to tattoo his dad
right on the forehead with a toothpick.

257
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:22,791
"Piece of shit," he wrote!

258
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:24,041
[both laughing]

259
00:13:24,125 --> 00:13:26,250
So is your dad a tattoo artist?

260
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:28,625
Nah, man! He's a Yakuza, dude!

261
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,458
- Then this little shit…
- [groans]

262
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:33,500
…decides to stand up for his old man
and tells my dad to lay off.

263
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:36,458
That's a lot of nerve
coming from a Sogabe.

264
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:38,666
Well, you pissed me off big time!

265
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:39,916
[Sogabe groans]

266
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,291
- [Kanemoto] So…
- [thug] Yeah?

267
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:42,500
I asked my old man

268
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:45,208
to give this guy the same tattoo!

269
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:46,125
PIECE OF SHIT

270
00:13:46,208 --> 00:13:50,125
That tattoo was done
by Kanemoto's dad, then?

271
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:51,208
That's right.

272
00:13:52,083 --> 00:13:53,833
They say tattoos done by amateurs

273
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:56,791
are difficult to remove, even for doctors,
because the depth of ink varies.

274
00:13:59,208 --> 00:14:00,041
[grunts]

275
00:14:00,125 --> 00:14:03,958
[Kanemoto] You and your old man
are gonna be called shit.

276
00:14:04,041 --> 00:14:06,083
- For the rest of your lives!
- [cries out]

277
00:14:06,166 --> 00:14:08,458
- [Kanemoto laughs]
- Whoa, that's crazy, man.

278
00:14:10,125 --> 00:14:12,166
- Boom!
- [thug groans]

279
00:14:14,166 --> 00:14:15,583
What was that again?

280
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,333
I…

281
00:14:18,416 --> 00:14:19,375
I'm sorry.

282
00:14:21,708 --> 00:14:25,875
[Karasuma] <i>Mr. Sogabe did a 6-year stretch</i>
<i>for Kanemoto and his pals,</i>

283
00:14:25,958 --> 00:14:27,916
<i>and I guess he got</i>
<i>the full treatment inside.</i>

284
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:31,833
The inmates made him eat someone's vomit.

285
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:35,208
They stabbed him with pencils
in places that wouldn't show.

286
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,041
They forced him to perform sexual favors.

287
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:41,541
Every day must've been hell for him.

288
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:46,500
Why would he go
anywhere near Kanemoto again?

289
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:53,041
[Kujo] It isn't easy to break out
of a vicious cycle.

290
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:56,125
Vicious cycle?

291
00:14:59,916 --> 00:15:01,416
[Kanemoto] Dude, this room

292
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:03,958
reeks to high heaven.

293
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:07,125
Yeah, I heard this place was
a stigmatized property.

294
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:10,833
Someone croaked here or offed himself,
and the corpse just rotted right there.

295
00:15:10,916 --> 00:15:11,875
Whoa.

296
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:15,625
I see.

297
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:19,166
They say the smell of a dead body
is hard to get rid of.

298
00:15:22,208 --> 00:15:24,375
Mmm, not bad.

299
00:15:24,875 --> 00:15:25,875
Even with the stink?

300
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:26,916
- Hey.
- Oh!

301
00:15:30,458 --> 00:15:35,166
Sogabe, old pal.
I apologize for all those insults.

302
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:36,666
Uh, it's okay.

303
00:15:38,208 --> 00:15:41,208
I've never been good at keeping my cool,
and I blew it again.

304
00:15:41,291 --> 00:15:43,833
- Sorry!
- No, yeah, sure. I get it.

305
00:15:43,916 --> 00:15:46,583
Um… I know I messed up.

306
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:50,208
No! We're always saying,
"Sogabe saved our asses a bunch of times."

307
00:15:50,291 --> 00:15:51,625
No. No, no, no.

308
00:15:51,708 --> 00:15:55,250
You're the kind of man who can
do me a favor, a guy I can rely on.

309
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:56,666
A favor?

310
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,291
Let me rent here.

311
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:02,958
We've been looking for a trap house
to cut and bag cocaine.

312
00:16:03,041 --> 00:16:05,041
[tense music playing]

313
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:06,708
Co… cocaine?

314
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:08,458
[Kanemoto] The order came from higher-ups.

315
00:16:08,541 --> 00:16:10,583
We gotta handle cocaine now.
We're in a jam.

316
00:16:12,125 --> 00:16:13,666
Help us out, will you?

317
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:18,541
[music fades]

318
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:28,500
[Sogabe] Uh, excuse me?

319
00:16:29,208 --> 00:16:30,541
Uh, where…

320
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:31,958
It was…

321
00:16:33,291 --> 00:16:35,541
- [Kujo] What's wrong, Mr. Sogabe?
- Oh!

322
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:38,708
Oh, was there a bag here I left behind?
Um…

323
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:40,000
Oh, shit.

324
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:42,000
[Kujo] This one here?

325
00:16:42,083 --> 00:16:44,333
[Sogabe] Huh? Oh! That's it.

326
00:16:45,166 --> 00:16:47,875
[chuckles] Thank you. Huh?

327
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:50,916
You know what's inside this, don't you?

328
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:54,458
Candies.

329
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,708
Hello, Mr. Sogabe. It's been a while.

330
00:16:57,791 --> 00:16:59,083
Huh?

331
00:16:59,166 --> 00:17:01,000
Oh, I'm Attorney Karasuma.
Do you remember me?

332
00:17:01,083 --> 00:17:05,875
Oh! Attorney Karasuma.
Thank you for that time. Uh, thank you.

333
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:09,166
If you have any trouble like that again,
I'm always ready to help.

334
00:17:09,250 --> 00:17:11,916
Oh. Yeah. Hmm.

335
00:17:14,125 --> 00:17:15,166
- Is there something?
- Nah.

336
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,583
Whatever's going on with me,

337
00:17:16,666 --> 00:17:19,125
it's nothing I can ask
a lawyer to deal with.

338
00:17:19,208 --> 00:17:20,541
Anyway, I'm broke.

339
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:25,125
And what do I know about the… the law?
Better to just to stay out of it, yeah.

340
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:26,166
Thanks.

341
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:28,916
[Karasuma] But aren't you being used
by Kanemoto again?

342
00:17:29,875 --> 00:17:31,250
No one's getting used!

343
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:32,291
Mmm.

344
00:17:33,958 --> 00:17:36,166
How dare you look down on me
just 'cause I'm stupid.

345
00:17:36,958 --> 00:17:39,666
[inhales] Shouldn't the older folks
look out for the younger ones?

346
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:41,208
- [Karasuma] Mr. Sogabe?
- What?

347
00:17:42,583 --> 00:17:44,166
I'm not looking down on you.

348
00:17:45,541 --> 00:17:46,375
Oh.

349
00:17:48,625 --> 00:17:49,500
Hmm.

350
00:17:49,583 --> 00:17:50,875
Oh, sorry.

351
00:17:50,958 --> 00:17:54,250
It's just, I've always been picked on
'cause I'm slow.

352
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:56,750
Since I was a kid,
that's what it's been like.

353
00:17:57,416 --> 00:17:58,958
No wonder you think that.

354
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:00,041
Mr. Sogabe.

355
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:01,291
Yes. Yes?

356
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:05,375
A lawyer's principal duty
is to listen to people.

357
00:18:05,958 --> 00:18:08,666
There's no charge for
the first consultation. It's on the house.

358
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:10,458
Come see us anytime you wish to.

359
00:18:12,041 --> 00:18:12,916
Oh.

360
00:18:14,333 --> 00:18:15,166
Huh.

361
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:17,166
Oh, thank you. Excuse me.

362
00:18:19,041 --> 00:18:20,583
[door opening, creaking]

363
00:18:20,666 --> 00:18:21,708
[door closes]

364
00:18:23,125 --> 00:18:24,625
Mr. Karasuma.

365
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:30,125
Do you have any idea why Sogabe
would hang out with Mr. Kanemoto?

366
00:18:31,208 --> 00:18:33,083
Because he's scared, I guess.

367
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:35,625
Because there's an advantage
to hanging out with him.

368
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:39,166
In Sogabe's world,
it can make a major difference.

369
00:18:39,791 --> 00:18:41,791
[tense music playing]

370
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:50,041
[man] Hey.

371
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,916
What's up with the dirty look?

372
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,041
Give us your cash or else.

373
00:18:58,958 --> 00:19:00,375
You know who I am?

374
00:19:01,125 --> 00:19:02,208
Say what?

375
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:04,250
You guys are lost.

376
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:05,333
[chuckles]

377
00:19:05,416 --> 00:19:07,750
Yo! Anything wrong, Sogabe?

378
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:09,500
[upbeat music playing]

379
00:19:10,291 --> 00:19:11,458
What?

380
00:19:12,333 --> 00:19:14,666
You got a problem with Mr. Sogabe?

381
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:16,250
Oh, uh…

382
00:19:16,875 --> 00:19:17,708
Hey!

383
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:19,666
- Here.
- Awesome work, thank you.

384
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:20,666
Sure.

385
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:24,541
We'll deal with this garbage!

386
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,208
Word.

387
00:19:26,291 --> 00:19:28,291
[men laughing]

388
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:31,583
[thug] Okay, assholes!
Step right this way.

389
00:19:31,666 --> 00:19:33,458
- [man grunting]
- [Kanemoto] Yes.

390
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:35,666
- Just what you wanted.
- [blows landing]

391
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:37,958
A room we can divide it up in.

392
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,083
- Yes, sir.
- [man grunts]

393
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:43,750
- Right. Oh, at your service, sir.
- [thugs laugh]

394
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:48,958
I rule!

395
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:51,208
I rule!

396
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:54,916
Kanemoto reigns supreme! Whoa!

397
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:55,916
[laughs]

398
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,125
I fuckin' rule!

399
00:19:58,708 --> 00:20:01,166
- You're in a good mood, Suguru.
- [chuckles]

400
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:02,166
Take that!

401
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:03,708
And that! [laughs]

402
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:08,500
You idiots… not only messed with
my colleague Sogabe,

403
00:20:08,583 --> 00:20:12,541
but you had the nerve
to try to sell on our territory?

404
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:13,791
[laughs]

405
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:15,583
Huh?

406
00:20:16,958 --> 00:20:18,625
Hmm? Huh?

407
00:20:18,708 --> 00:20:21,500
These guys look kind of dead. Hey!

408
00:20:21,583 --> 00:20:23,416
We meant to half-kill them, but

409
00:20:23,958 --> 00:20:26,541
I'd say we pretty much
killed them for good.

410
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:28,791
[chuckles] Okay, so they bought the farm.

411
00:20:29,291 --> 00:20:33,375
It doesn't matter
'cause Sogabe can always take the fall.

412
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,125
- Genius!
- Huh?

413
00:20:36,916 --> 00:20:38,833
Amazing how useful a Sogabe can be.

414
00:20:38,916 --> 00:20:39,791
[laughs]

415
00:20:39,875 --> 00:20:41,458
Brilliant! Brilliant!

416
00:20:41,541 --> 00:20:43,041
[woman] Suguru!

417
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:45,458
Miyoko? Miyoko!

418
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:49,375
Let's go home.
I'm gonna make your favorite tonight.

419
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:51,333
Sweet curry hot pot with noodles!

420
00:20:51,416 --> 00:20:52,708
Yes, sir!

421
00:20:52,791 --> 00:20:53,750
[laughs]

422
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,333
Deal with the mess, will ya?

423
00:20:55,416 --> 00:20:56,875
- [thug 1] Sure.
- [thug 2] You got it.

424
00:20:57,583 --> 00:20:59,125
- [Miyoko] You're late!
- [Kanemoto laughs]

425
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:03,291
Today it's Miyoko! Miyoko and me!

426
00:21:03,375 --> 00:21:04,750
And curry makes three!

427
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:06,000
[laughs]

428
00:21:08,958 --> 00:21:10,333
Mmm. Mmm!

429
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:11,333
Mmm.

430
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:14,250
[Karasuma] Just watching you eat
makes me feel full.

431
00:21:14,333 --> 00:21:15,291
[chuckles]

432
00:21:15,375 --> 00:21:16,916
[Yakushimae chuckles]

433
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,625
So I guess I can have
all this pepper pork stir-fry?

434
00:21:19,708 --> 00:21:21,208
Go right ahead.

435
00:21:23,125 --> 00:21:25,666
So, you said you wanted to talk?

436
00:21:25,750 --> 00:21:27,208
- Mmm.
- Well, let's hear it.

437
00:21:27,291 --> 00:21:29,958
Um, you remember Sota Sogabe, right?

438
00:21:30,041 --> 00:21:30,916
Of course.

439
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:34,583
Right after he got out, I gave him
the standard post-release support.

440
00:21:34,666 --> 00:21:37,625
Helped him with a job,
got him a place to live, but…

441
00:21:37,708 --> 00:21:41,291
Uh, it couldn't have been even a month
before he just went off the radar.

442
00:21:41,875 --> 00:21:44,208
And I heard he's ghosted his parents too.

443
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:46,791
He's… committed another crime, I think.

444
00:21:47,666 --> 00:21:49,708
Huh? You sure?

445
00:21:50,541 --> 00:21:52,541
Yeah. I'd say for sure.

446
00:21:54,083 --> 00:21:57,375
Ugh! Sota Sogabe!

447
00:21:57,458 --> 00:22:00,333
That idiot! Why would he do that?

448
00:22:01,041 --> 00:22:03,291
Anyway, I'd like to ask for your help

449
00:22:03,375 --> 00:22:04,791
in getting him reintegrated.

450
00:22:04,875 --> 00:22:06,833
[sighs] Dude's a fool.

451
00:22:06,916 --> 00:22:09,833
Don't say that. Come on.
Let's team up and help the guy.

452
00:22:09,916 --> 00:22:12,416
Mr. Kujo would want that too.
I'm sure of it.

453
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,416
Another beer please, thank you.

454
00:22:17,125 --> 00:22:18,416
Here you go.

455
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,625
[woman 1] Thank you!

456
00:22:19,708 --> 00:22:21,125
- [Sogabe] Thanks.
- [woman 1 giggles]

457
00:22:21,208 --> 00:22:22,541
- [woman 2 chuckles]
- See ya! Bye!

458
00:22:22,625 --> 00:22:25,708
- [chorus of goodbyes]
- [Sogabe] <i>The weed buyers look happy.</i>

459
00:22:25,791 --> 00:22:27,791
[upbeat music playing]

460
00:22:27,875 --> 00:22:30,625
[sniffs, groans]

461
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,625
Good stuff. Gimme three packets.

462
00:22:33,708 --> 00:22:34,750
Sure.

463
00:22:36,291 --> 00:22:37,166
Okay.

464
00:22:37,250 --> 00:22:38,416
Here you go.

465
00:22:39,708 --> 00:22:40,541
Oh.

466
00:22:41,125 --> 00:22:43,541
- Also, this is my pee.
- [man chuckles]

467
00:22:43,625 --> 00:22:46,083
A good luck charm for my urine test,
huh? Thank you.

468
00:22:46,166 --> 00:22:47,250
Welcome.

469
00:22:48,041 --> 00:22:49,041
Have a good time!

470
00:22:49,666 --> 00:22:52,500
[Sogabe] <i>The cokeheads are party animals</i>
<i>with money to burn.</i>

471
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:54,875
You wanna fight?

472
00:22:54,958 --> 00:22:55,791
No! No, I don't.

473
00:22:55,875 --> 00:22:58,458
- Give me the meth!
- Sorry. We actually don't sell any meth.

474
00:22:58,541 --> 00:23:00,541
Just give it to me!

475
00:23:00,625 --> 00:23:02,958
I've got the money!

476
00:23:03,041 --> 00:23:06,125
- Sha-la! La-la-la-la!
- Uh, excuse me!

477
00:23:06,208 --> 00:23:08,833
<i>Speed freaks are mostly</i>
<i>the old and the poor.</i>

478
00:23:08,916 --> 00:23:10,375
[addict continues singing/screaming]

479
00:23:10,458 --> 00:23:12,041
[Sogabe] <i>The bottom's a bummer.</i>

480
00:23:12,125 --> 00:23:14,000
[addict screaming and crying]

481
00:23:15,958 --> 00:23:18,208
[Sogabe] <i>I know my current job is wrong,</i>

482
00:23:18,291 --> 00:23:21,375
<i>but at least I'm giving people</i>
<i>what they want and making them happy.</i>

483
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,166
<i>When I was mugging older guys</i>
<i>eight years ago,</i>

484
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:26,708
<i>I felt bad for the victims,</i>
<i>and it made me sick.</i>

485
00:23:28,375 --> 00:23:30,500
[detective 1] You must be Sota Sogabe.

486
00:23:31,083 --> 00:23:32,416
[detective 2] Have a minute?

487
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:34,041
[music fades]

488
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:38,333
- Hey! Hey, wait up!
- [detective 1] Sogabe!

489
00:23:38,416 --> 00:23:41,291
- [Sogabe grunts, moans] Ow.
- [detective 1] Come here!

490
00:23:41,375 --> 00:23:42,250
[Sogabe] I'm sorry.

491
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:45,458
[little girl] <i>Wow, so cute!</i>

492
00:23:45,541 --> 00:23:48,041
[woman] <i>Come on, Rino.</i>
<i>Say something to Daddy.</i>

493
00:23:48,625 --> 00:23:50,916
<i>She's beautiful! I love her. Thank you!</i>

494
00:23:51,416 --> 00:23:52,750
<i>Have a nice time at work!</i>

495
00:23:53,541 --> 00:23:54,666
[woman] <i>Take care.</i>

496
00:23:55,166 --> 00:23:56,333
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

497
00:23:56,416 --> 00:23:59,000
[woman] <i>Bye-bye. See you.</i>

498
00:24:02,375 --> 00:24:04,083
Hello. Kujo here.

499
00:24:04,166 --> 00:24:05,083
[sighs]

500
00:24:05,583 --> 00:24:08,333
Sota Sogabe has been arrested.

501
00:24:08,416 --> 00:24:09,333
[Kujo] <i>On what charges?</i>

502
00:24:10,708 --> 00:24:11,958
Possession of weed

503
00:24:13,291 --> 00:24:14,416
and cocaine as well.

504
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:17,375
Cocaine?

505
00:24:19,083 --> 00:24:23,625
Three grams of cocaine and four grams
of marijuana buds were found at your home.

506
00:24:23,708 --> 00:24:26,958
The bust was after the sorting,
so luckily the amounts are small.

507
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:29,750
[Karasuma] But with your prior,
Mr. Sogabe,

508
00:24:29,833 --> 00:24:32,958
you're looking at some prison time,
no matter what.

509
00:24:34,125 --> 00:24:35,958
Have you heard, by the way,

510
00:24:36,750 --> 00:24:39,125
that Mr. Kanemoto was arrested
as an accomplice?

511
00:24:39,750 --> 00:24:41,166
Kanemoto got busted?

512
00:24:42,375 --> 00:24:44,000
No, I wasn't aware.

513
00:24:45,208 --> 00:24:46,625
[Karasuma] Mr. Sogabe.

514
00:24:47,208 --> 00:24:50,333
Why don't you… treat this situation
as a chance to come clean?

515
00:24:51,625 --> 00:24:52,500
Come clean?

516
00:24:52,583 --> 00:24:55,666
Tell them what really happened
with the robbery and the drugs.

517
00:24:55,750 --> 00:24:58,916
Tell them that Kanemoto was threatening
you and that you didn't have a choice.

518
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:04,750
Do you remember Yakushimae,
the social worker who helped you?

519
00:25:06,458 --> 00:25:09,750
I asked her to place you
in a shelter temporarily

520
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:13,125
so Kanemoto can't get his hands on you
if you make bail.

521
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:16,416
You can break the vicious cycle here.

522
00:25:17,875 --> 00:25:20,375
If you're on board,
I'll do everything possible to help you.

523
00:25:20,458 --> 00:25:22,375
- That's a bad idea.
- What?

524
00:25:24,375 --> 00:25:25,666
[sighs, smacks lips]

525
00:25:26,833 --> 00:25:27,875
Mr. Sogabe.

526
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:32,208
You are not to say a thing
about Suguru Kanemoto.

527
00:25:32,833 --> 00:25:34,458
Cop to the charges. Don't mention anybody.

528
00:25:34,541 --> 00:25:36,041
What are you saying?

529
00:25:36,125 --> 00:25:38,375
Giving that kind of instruction
could get you disbarred.

530
00:25:38,458 --> 00:25:40,875
No one's gonna know
as long as we all stay quiet.

531
00:25:41,708 --> 00:25:42,708
I won't be a part of this.

532
00:25:43,916 --> 00:25:44,916
So go.

533
00:25:51,875 --> 00:25:55,125
Attorney Kujo, you're making him do
the same thing all over again.

534
00:25:56,375 --> 00:25:58,958
Why are you covering for
a scumbag like Kanemoto?

535
00:25:59,041 --> 00:26:02,166
This will leave Mr. Sogabe
stuck like this forever.

536
00:26:02,666 --> 00:26:04,541
What will this do to his parents?

537
00:26:04,625 --> 00:26:05,500
[Sogabe] It's okay.

538
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:07,375
What?

539
00:26:07,958 --> 00:26:08,958
Yeah.

540
00:26:09,625 --> 00:26:11,625
I, uh, said it's okay.

541
00:26:13,750 --> 00:26:15,375
I'll take the blame for all of it.

542
00:26:15,958 --> 00:26:17,291
[melancholy music playing]

543
00:26:17,375 --> 00:26:18,541
You know,

544
00:26:20,291 --> 00:26:22,000
I often remember

545
00:26:22,083 --> 00:26:24,375
this track day at school.

546
00:26:24,875 --> 00:26:26,041
[cheering and shouting]

547
00:26:26,125 --> 00:26:29,166
[Sogabe] <i>I was… a total klutz.</i>

548
00:26:29,791 --> 00:26:31,708
<i>I always came last in races.</i>

549
00:26:32,208 --> 00:26:37,291
<i>Everyone at the track would be cheering</i>
<i>and clapping for the runners.</i>

550
00:26:38,458 --> 00:26:41,708
<i>I looked around, desperate to see my mom.</i>

551
00:26:43,791 --> 00:26:44,791
<i>And then…</i>

552
00:26:46,250 --> 00:26:50,958
<i>There she was with her head down</i>
<i>like it was the end of the world.</i>

553
00:26:53,791 --> 00:26:56,625
I think she was embarrassed and frustrated

554
00:26:57,208 --> 00:26:58,208
because of me.

555
00:26:58,916 --> 00:27:00,458
[sighs]

556
00:27:00,541 --> 00:27:04,125
So if a piece of trash like me
can actually be of use to someone,

557
00:27:04,208 --> 00:27:05,250
just tell me what to do.

558
00:27:06,083 --> 00:27:07,958
- Mr. Sogabe--
- I understand perfectly.

559
00:27:08,708 --> 00:27:11,916
So, that's how we'll be proceeding.

560
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:15,958
Are you sure about this?

561
00:27:22,541 --> 00:27:24,083
[music fades]

562
00:27:25,541 --> 00:27:26,833
[cop] Kanemoto.

563
00:27:27,583 --> 00:27:29,791
Let's hear you say something already, huh?

564
00:27:34,416 --> 00:27:37,166
Don't even dream that
a half-assed little brat like you can…

565
00:27:37,250 --> 00:27:38,250
[bangs table]

566
00:27:38,333 --> 00:27:41,166
…clam up when you're dealing with
a guy like me.

567
00:27:41,250 --> 00:27:45,000
[dramatic sting]

568
00:27:47,041 --> 00:27:48,416
Mr. Kujo.

569
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:51,958
If you defend Mr. Sogabe
and Mr. Kanemoto simultaneously,

570
00:27:52,041 --> 00:27:54,000
you're creating a conflict of interest.

571
00:27:54,708 --> 00:27:57,333
An attorney should always
avoid situations like this.

572
00:27:58,125 --> 00:28:00,291
Let's say I obtain a result
that's good for both of them.

573
00:28:00,375 --> 00:28:02,416
Neither will report me
to the bar association,

574
00:28:02,500 --> 00:28:04,208
and there won't be a hearing.

575
00:28:04,291 --> 00:28:06,041
The problem goes away.

576
00:28:06,541 --> 00:28:08,791
So this is how you handle your cases?

577
00:28:09,750 --> 00:28:10,958
[guard] Go in.

578
00:28:18,583 --> 00:28:22,041
[Kujo] You look worn out, Mr. Kanemoto.

579
00:28:22,125 --> 00:28:23,083
[sighs]

580
00:28:23,166 --> 00:28:26,041
It's my first time being interrogated.

581
00:28:28,625 --> 00:28:29,708
But more importantly,

582
00:28:30,833 --> 00:28:32,500
did that bastard Sogabe rat me out?

583
00:28:32,583 --> 00:28:33,583
No.

584
00:28:34,375 --> 00:28:35,583
Certainly not.

585
00:28:40,916 --> 00:28:42,375
Look, Mr. Kanemoto.

586
00:28:44,083 --> 00:28:47,541
The cops will play a lot of head games
with you over the next 20 days.

587
00:28:48,625 --> 00:28:51,416
They want to catch you in a lie,
so don't open your mouth at all.

588
00:28:51,916 --> 00:28:52,791
Mum's the word, right?

589
00:28:53,833 --> 00:28:55,166
Yes. Yes, sir.

590
00:28:56,208 --> 00:28:58,583
[Kujo] Attorneys can see their clients
whenever they want.

591
00:28:59,250 --> 00:29:01,791
You start to lose it, I can come see you.

592
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:05,958
Just make sure you clam up for 20 days.

593
00:29:06,541 --> 00:29:07,458
If you manage that,

594
00:29:07,541 --> 00:29:09,458
you'll be out in 20 days
without indictment

595
00:29:09,541 --> 00:29:10,833
pending further investigation.

596
00:29:10,916 --> 00:29:12,958
After that,
odds are they'll drop the whole thing.

597
00:29:13,041 --> 00:29:14,000
Got it?

598
00:29:14,583 --> 00:29:15,750
Yeah, got it.

599
00:29:16,625 --> 00:29:18,625
[Kujo] Judging from what
the detectives told me,

600
00:29:18,708 --> 00:29:23,125
the cops don't have much in the way
of evidence of your involvement.

601
00:29:23,208 --> 00:29:25,750
If they try to threaten

602
00:29:25,833 --> 00:29:28,875
or to sweet talk you,
those are signs of weakness.

603
00:29:28,958 --> 00:29:30,833
Means we're gonna win. Remember that.

604
00:29:30,916 --> 00:29:32,833
Yes, sir!

605
00:29:35,083 --> 00:29:38,666
A notebook like this is forbidden
because the wire can be a weapon.

606
00:29:39,166 --> 00:29:41,250
I can get you a regular notebook later.

607
00:29:41,833 --> 00:29:44,125
Write whatever they say to you
during questioning every day.

608
00:29:44,208 --> 00:29:45,208
[Kanemoto] Understood.

609
00:29:45,291 --> 00:29:47,583
Make it one page for each day.

610
00:29:47,666 --> 00:29:49,750
You're gonna be out in 20 days,
so be strong.

611
00:29:49,833 --> 00:29:51,708
Yes. Yes, sir.

612
00:29:51,791 --> 00:29:53,041
I'll do my best.

613
00:29:53,125 --> 00:29:56,583
[Karasuma] You tormented Mr. Sogabe
into submission with your violence.

614
00:29:56,666 --> 00:29:59,916
But look at how obedient you are
now that you're in a cage.

615
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,333
Huh?

616
00:30:01,416 --> 00:30:04,125
When you think someone's weak,
you like to bare your fangs,

617
00:30:04,208 --> 00:30:06,791
but you bow down to the strong,
people like lawyers.

618
00:30:07,791 --> 00:30:10,250
Sneaky little cowards like you
are the lowest of the low.

619
00:30:10,833 --> 00:30:13,250
Whoa. Mr. Kujo,
what the hell's this guy's deal?

620
00:30:13,833 --> 00:30:15,833
[sighs] He's a lawyer working for me.

621
00:30:16,625 --> 00:30:19,708
I'm here with Attorney Kujo
because it comes with the job.

622
00:30:20,208 --> 00:30:22,750
But that doesn't mean
I have to like creeps like you.

623
00:30:22,833 --> 00:30:26,416
Right back at you, shithead!
Get rid of him! Attorney Kujo!

624
00:30:26,500 --> 00:30:28,916
No. That I won't do.

625
00:30:29,708 --> 00:30:31,666
What the hell is wrong with you?

626
00:30:31,750 --> 00:30:33,625
- Don't give me this shit!
- [guard] In the chair!

627
00:30:33,708 --> 00:30:35,250
- [guard] What are you doing?
- You'll see!

628
00:30:35,333 --> 00:30:36,333
- Easy.
- Don't mess with me!

629
00:30:36,416 --> 00:30:38,375
- Calm down! Get a grip!
- Don't touch me!

630
00:30:38,458 --> 00:30:40,166
- Don't give me this crap!
- Calm down, I said!

631
00:30:40,250 --> 00:30:41,250
[Kanemoto] Piece of shit!

632
00:30:41,333 --> 00:30:42,166
[guard] Knock it off!

633
00:30:42,250 --> 00:30:43,583
[Kanemoto] Don't mess with me!

634
00:30:44,166 --> 00:30:45,583
- [guard] Come on!
- [Kanemoto] Miyoko!

635
00:30:45,666 --> 00:30:47,666
[upbeat music playing]

636
00:30:48,833 --> 00:30:50,458
[Yakushimae] Hey, sleazebag!

637
00:30:50,541 --> 00:30:51,416
Hello to you.

638
00:30:51,500 --> 00:30:53,000
What the hell are you playing at?

639
00:30:54,166 --> 00:30:56,291
Sogabe's taking all the blame
because of you,

640
00:30:56,375 --> 00:30:59,208
and that monster
Suguru Kanemoto gets off the hook.

641
00:30:59,291 --> 00:31:00,750
God, what's wrong with you?

642
00:31:00,833 --> 00:31:02,291
What are you thinking?

643
00:31:03,125 --> 00:31:06,833
Just trying to get a lighter sentence
for Mr. Sogabe, that's all.

644
00:31:07,458 --> 00:31:08,708
What?

645
00:31:08,791 --> 00:31:10,041
[Kujo] <i>He has a criminal record,</i>

646
00:31:10,125 --> 00:31:12,208
<i>so he can't avoid</i>
<i>another stretch in prison.</i>

647
00:31:12,708 --> 00:31:16,166
<i>On top of which, when you reoffend</i>
<i>within five years of your release,</i>

648
00:31:16,250 --> 00:31:17,625
<i>you get extra time.</i>

649
00:31:19,208 --> 00:31:21,208
Attorney Karasuma,
is this man telling the truth?

650
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:23,333
Uh, yeah.

651
00:31:24,708 --> 00:31:27,583
So, the deciding factor
in the trial will be

652
00:31:28,166 --> 00:31:29,666
whether Sogabe had the drugs

653
00:31:29,750 --> 00:31:31,750
because he intended to distribute them
for profit

654
00:31:31,833 --> 00:31:35,583
or whether we can convince the court
that it was a simple case of possession

655
00:31:35,666 --> 00:31:36,625
for personal use.

656
00:31:37,208 --> 00:31:39,000
What's the difference between the two?

657
00:31:39,708 --> 00:31:42,208
The cops found baggies
and a digital scale in his home,

658
00:31:42,291 --> 00:31:44,083
so they charged him with trafficking,

659
00:31:44,166 --> 00:31:46,250
and they're aiming for
a three-year prison sentence.

660
00:31:46,833 --> 00:31:49,708
But if it were a case
of simple possession,

661
00:31:49,791 --> 00:31:51,791
the sentence could be half as long.

662
00:31:51,875 --> 00:31:53,083
[Kujo] Exactly.

663
00:31:53,166 --> 00:31:55,250
If there's nothing connecting
Kanemoto to the crime,

664
00:31:55,333 --> 00:31:57,125
it's harder to prove
an intent to distribute.

665
00:31:57,208 --> 00:32:00,583
Therefore, the case will lean towards
simple possession.

666
00:32:03,666 --> 00:32:05,375
Does that answer your question now?

667
00:32:05,458 --> 00:32:06,416
[scoffs]

668
00:32:06,500 --> 00:32:09,875
I'm not here to get a lecture
in legal statutes.

669
00:32:09,958 --> 00:32:12,791
I wanted to say
that this is ethically wrong.

670
00:32:14,125 --> 00:32:15,166
Ethically?

671
00:32:15,250 --> 00:32:17,500
Sogabe had no clue
what he was involved in.

672
00:32:17,583 --> 00:32:21,791
Kanemoto was using that kid
and controlling every last thing he did.

673
00:32:21,875 --> 00:32:24,166
How they're treating him now
is just cruel.

674
00:32:25,458 --> 00:32:26,958
[Kujo] He's not clueless.

675
00:32:27,458 --> 00:32:28,333
Huh?

676
00:32:28,416 --> 00:32:32,291
Mr. Sogabe is way more reasonable
than anyone gives him credit for.

677
00:32:32,875 --> 00:32:34,708
[Yakushimae] What? Reasonable?

678
00:32:35,833 --> 00:32:38,083
Course you're the expert on reasonable.

679
00:32:38,166 --> 00:32:40,125
You tell vulnerable boys what to do,

680
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:43,166
and you exploit their weakness
to help a gang of thugs.

681
00:32:44,166 --> 00:32:45,875
I call that immoral!

682
00:32:46,416 --> 00:32:49,291
I thought lawyers were supposed
to help the neediest?

683
00:32:50,958 --> 00:32:53,666
Ethically,
what you're doing is outrageous.

684
00:32:54,166 --> 00:32:55,416
It's unacceptable!

685
00:32:56,166 --> 00:32:57,708
[music fades]

686
00:33:02,083 --> 00:33:03,333
[door opens]

687
00:33:04,625 --> 00:33:05,666
[door slams]

688
00:33:07,708 --> 00:33:10,166
Do you think so too, Attorney Karasuma?

689
00:33:11,500 --> 00:33:14,875
Well, I'm not totally persuaded
that it's immoral.

690
00:33:14,958 --> 00:33:16,583
But… [sighs]

691
00:33:16,666 --> 00:33:17,541
But?

692
00:33:17,625 --> 00:33:20,333
I've got my own plan
for how to save Mr. Sogabe.

693
00:33:28,458 --> 00:33:30,333
- [sighs]
- [door opens]

694
00:33:30,416 --> 00:33:31,916
[cell phone buzzes]

695
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,125
[door closes]

696
00:33:35,833 --> 00:33:37,666
Hello. This is Kujo.

697
00:33:38,250 --> 00:33:40,083
[Mibu] So, how'd it go?

698
00:33:41,125 --> 00:33:44,791
I've decided to have Mr. Sogabe
take the blame for everything.

699
00:33:44,875 --> 00:33:47,375
<i>I'm making him leave Mr. Kanemoto</i>
<i>out of it.</i>

700
00:33:47,458 --> 00:33:48,666
In return,

701
00:33:49,375 --> 00:33:52,291
Mr. Kanemoto keeps his mouth shut
and gets cut loose in 20 days.

702
00:33:52,375 --> 00:33:53,291
[scoffs]

703
00:33:53,791 --> 00:33:54,958
Nice work.

704
00:33:56,333 --> 00:34:00,541
If you actually swing this,
I'd say you're a damn genius.

705
00:34:00,625 --> 00:34:01,833
[chuckles]

706
00:34:01,916 --> 00:34:03,916
[upbeat music playing]

707
00:34:55,916 --> 00:34:57,916
Okay, boys! Let's get lunch!

708
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:58,916
Come on.

709
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:02,000
[indistinct chatter]

710
00:35:11,666 --> 00:35:13,125
[Karasuma] Excuse me, sir?

711
00:35:13,916 --> 00:35:15,916
You're Mr. Sota Sogabe's father, right?

712
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:16,833
PIECE OF SHIT

713
00:35:16,916 --> 00:35:18,250
Yeah. You are?

714
00:35:18,833 --> 00:35:20,666
My name's Karasuma. I'm an attorney.

715
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:25,416
I want to help your son escape
from the control of Suguru Kanemoto.

716
00:35:26,750 --> 00:35:28,541
Would you be willing to help me?

717
00:35:33,458 --> 00:35:35,541
[closing theme song playing]

718
00:38:11,333 --> 00:38:12,541
[music fades]
